data.title: Input.is_key_pressed() method not working properly for some keys
data.body:
Using : Godot_v2.0.2_stable_x11.64 on linuxmint 17.2

InputEvent.scancode is returning wrong values for some keys and these keys also don't work with
Input.is_key_pressed() method. For example KEY_BACKSPACE is working but KEY_ENTER is not working with Input.is_key_pressed() method. InputEvent.scancode value is a 8 digit integer for both of KEY_BACKSPACE and KEY_ENTER. Besides KEY_SPACE seems to be working as expected.

Press "enter", "space" and "backspace" to replicate

Sample code : 

```
extends Node2D

func _ready():  
    set_process_input(true)

func _input(event):
    if event.type == InputEvent.KEY && event.pressed:
        print("\n\n \n ----- ----- ----- ----- ----- ----- -----")
        var scancode = event.scancode
        print('scancode ' + str(scancode))
        var unicode = event.unicode
        print('unicode ' + str(unicode))

        print("\n ----- ----- ----- ----- ----- ----- -----")
        print('CHECKING KEY_ENTER')
        var reported_scancode_for_enter = 16777221
        print ('scancode when "enter" pressed is : ' + str(reported_scancode_for_enter))
        print('value of constant for KEY_ENTER is : ' + str(KEY_ENTER))
        if(scancode == reported_scancode_for_enter):
            print('ENTER IS PRESSED')
        if(Input.is_key_pressed(KEY_ENTER)):
            print('is_key_pressed for KEY_ENTER is working')

        print("\n ----- ----- ----- ----- ----- ----- -----")
        print('CHECKING KEY_BACKSPACE')
        var reported_scancode_for_backspace = 16777220
        print ('scancode when "backspace" pressed is : ' + str(reported_scancode_for_backspace))
        print('value of constant for KEY_BACKSPACE is : ' + str(KEY_BACKSPACE))
        if(scancode == reported_scancode_for_backspace):
            print('BACKSPACE IS PRESSED')
        if(Input.is_key_pressed(KEY_BACKSPACE)):
            print('is_key_pressed for KEY_BACKSPACE is working')

        print("\n ----- ----- ----- ----- ----- ----- -----")
        print('CHECKING KEY_SPACE')
        var reported_scancode_for_space = 32
        print ('scancode when "space" pressed is : ' + str(reported_scancode_for_space))
        print('value of constant for KEY_SPACE is : ' + str(KEY_SPACE))
        if(scancode == reported_scancode_for_space):
            print('SPACE IS PRESSED')
        if(Input.is_key_pressed(KEY_SPACE)):
            print('is_key_pressed for KEY_SPACE is working')
```

data.title: Added possibility to strip left and right to strip_edges
data.body:
Added two optional parameters to `strip_edges` in order to strip only left and only right part of the string. This are defaulted to true to ensure compatibility with current stripping mechanic.

Also optimizes the call by replacing calls to `length()` with a local variable

Fixes #968 

If needed I can squish commits.

data.title: Test game closes on using ssl-enabled host.
data.body:
**Operating system or device - Godot version:**
Ubuntu 15.10 64-bit
branch: master
head: 8a45936

**Issue description** (what happened, and what was expected):
I have built the godot source using `$ scons platform=x11 openssl=builtin`. A test game closes upon connecting to an ssl-enabled host. Unfortunately, there's no error message info displaying on gdb. On `HTTPRequest` node, you can test this url `https://godot-ssl-test.firebaseio.com/.json`. Upon completion, it is expected that you should receive a response:

``` json
{"test":{"message":"ok"}}
```

On the other hand, no problem upon requesting valid url with `http` as the scheme.

**Steps to reproduce:**
1. Create new project.
2. Add scene.
3. Add HTTPRequest node as root.
4. Connect "request_completed" signal.
5. Perform request using `https://godot-ssl-test.firebaseio.com/.json`.
6. Run current scene. _(expectation: the game closes.)_
7. If expectation at `step 6` fails, you should receive a response mentioned above and the game does not close.

data.title: Arrays can not be resetted in the inspector, will not work if you create them with 'export' in gdscript, but not assign them manually in the inspector
data.body:
wow, do i have the honor of being the 1000th issue? 

I just noticed that Array type variables can not be resetted, like other types of variables in godot:
![arrayss](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6495061/15098428/9146f456-1535-11e6-972c-63955a44dcba.png)

Whats worse is that if you make an array in gdscript like this:

```
export var myArray = [1,2,8,4]
for test in myArray:print('whyy',test)

```

and forget to give it any values in the inspector, the array will simply be empty. The for loop will not print at all!

In essence array type variables have no default value that they can be resetted to. They do not work at all if you have not assigned anything to them in the inspector, while they have the export tagged in gdscript.

This is inconsistent with strings, ints, floats and what have you. :) 

So this is a problem with them in both gdscript and the inspector.

data.title: Button pressed style never appears
data.body:
Operating system or device - Godot version: Xubuntu 14.04.4 - Godot 2.0.2
Issue description (what happened, and what was expected):
I have a project where I want to use Buttons with custom images. If I set up  different properties in the Custom Styles section of the button and I run the project the pressed style never appears. All of the other styles are working except for the pressed style, (No matter if I use StyleBoxFlat or StyleboxTexture!)
And it's quite interesting because if I specify Custom Colors for the button the Font Color Pressed seems working!
I was expecting the pressed image appear too when the button is pressed, not just the font color change.
I was looking around the godot source I have noticed that in button.cpp in void Button::_notification(int p_what) function, first the pressed style is drawn in the switch( get_draw_mode() ) section, but then:

``` cpp
if (has_focus()) {

    Ref<StyleBox> style = get_stylebox("focus");
    style->draw(ci,Rect2(Point2(),size));
}
```

overwrites the button appearance. An unfortunately the button has the focus after being clicked and therefore the focused style is drawn "overwriting" the pressed style. IMHO the focused style only should be drawn for a button if it's not pressed, but has the focus. (For example the user navigating with the tab key and the button has the focus then the focused style should be active, but when he hits the space, and therefore presses the button, the pressed style should appear.)
